"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-11-07-europa-league-dessers-salvages-draw-for-rangers-against-olympiacos\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Cyriel Dessers rescued a point for Rangers as they held Olympiacos to a 1-1 draw in Piraeus on Thursday night.  Morocco international Ayoub El Kaabi gave the hosts the lead four minutes before the hour mark.  Dessers, however, equalised for Rangers in the 64th minutes with Vaclav Cerny providing the assist.  The Nigeria international has now scored nine goals and registered three assists in 18 appearances across all competitions for Philippe Clement's side this season.  He was replaced by Hamza Igamane five minutes from time.  His compatriot, Leon Balogun was an unused substitute for Rangers.  NPFL: Kano Pillars ready for Bendel Insurance clash  UEFA rankings: Man City, Madrid lead as Chelsea overtake Barcelona, Arsenal, Man Utd [Top 20]  Europa League top scorers  Europa League: Three Super Eagles Stars to clash in quarter-finals  Europa League: Gabriel Agbonlahor hails two clubs for saving Premier League  Europa League: All quarter-final fixtures confirmed  Europa League: How Nottingham Forest can beat FC Midtylland - Aina  Europa League: Aina upbeat Nottingham Forest can progress ahead FC Midtylland  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"